# Java & Quarkus Standards

- Target Java 25 features (records, sealed classes, pattern matching, etc.)
- Use Quarkus REST (`quarkus-rest`) idioms and best practices
- Use descriptive method and variable names in camelCase
- Implement RESTful API design patterns (proper HTTP methods, status codes)
- Use `@Inject` via constructor injection, never field injection

# Testing

- Write unit tests with JUnit 5 and `@QuarkusTest`
- Write integration tests with `@QuarkusIntegrationTest`
- Use REST Assured for endpoint testing

# Build

- Manage dependencies via Maven (`pom.xml`); use `./mvnw` to build
- Quarkus BOM version is managed in `<quarkus.platform.version>`
